 },
 "html": "<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-5355\" src=\"/media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"hot cross bun pudding\" width=\"530\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"/media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-1024x768.jpeg 1024w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-600x450.jpeg 600w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-300x225.jpeg 300w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-768x576.jpeg 768w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-750x563.jpeg 750w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-500x375.jpeg 500w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-380x285.jpeg 380w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-760x570.jpeg 760w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00-800x600.jpeg 800w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.50.00.jpeg 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px\"></p>\n<p>With Easter just around the corner, it's time to do something with those hot cross buns.</p>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>6 hot cross buns</li>\n<li>Apricot jam</li>\n<li>Butter</li>\n<li>500 ml cream</li>\n<li>1 tin Ideal milk</li>\n<li>250 ml milk</li>\n<li>125 ml castor sugar</li>\n<li>5 eggs</li>\n<li>5 ml caramel flavouring (vanilla essence)</li>\n<li>Flake chocolates</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-5357\" src=\"/media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-768x1024.jpeg\" alt=\"hot cross buns\" width=\"530\" height=\"707\" srcset=\"/media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-768x1024.jpeg 768w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-600x800.jpeg 600w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-225x300.jpeg 225w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-750x1000.jpeg 750w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-380x507.jpeg 380w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-760x1013.jpeg 760w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53-800x1067.jpeg 800w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.53.jpeg 960w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px\"></h3>\n<h3>Method</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Cut the hot cross buns through and spread generously with butter and apricot jam.</li>\n<li>Layer them like roof tiles, overlapping, in a greased ovenproof dish.</li>\n<li>Whisk the rest of the ingredients (except the Flakes) together and pour over the hot cross buns.</li>\n<li>Let it stand for half an hour to soak in.</li>\n<li>Bake uncovered for 40 minutes at 180 degrees celsius.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle Flakes over and eat with ice cream or custard.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-5356\" src=\"/media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-1024x768.jpeg\" alt=\"hot cross bun pudding\" width=\"530\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"/media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-1024x768.jpeg 1024w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-600x450.jpeg 600w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-300x225.jpeg 300w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-768x576.jpeg 768w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-750x563.jpeg 750w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-500x375.jpeg 500w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-380x285.jpeg 380w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-760x570.jpeg 760w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58-800x600.jpeg 800w, /media/uploads/2019/03/WhatsApp-Image-2019-03-25-at-21.49.58.jpeg 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px\"></p>"
